doc.ContractDescription: X-RAY SPECTRUM AND PULSATIONS OF THE OLD GAMMA-RAY PULSAR J1836+5925 THE BRIGHT GAMMA-RAY SOURCE 3EG J1835+5918 WAS IDENTIFIED AS A GAMMA-RAY PULSAR PSR J1836+5925 BY THE FERMI OBSERVATORY. WITH THE AGE OF 1.8 MYR, IT IS ONE OF THE OLDEST GAMMA-RAY PULSARS KNOWN. SIMILAR TO THE FAMOUS GEMINGA PULSAR, PSR J1836+5925 IS A RADIO-QUIET X-RAY SOURCE. PREVIOUS X-RAY OBSERVATIONS HAVE SHOWN THAT ITS SPECTRUM CONSISTS OF A THERMAL COMPONENT EMITTED FROM THE NEUTRON STAR SURFACE AND NONTHERMAL COMPONENT EMITTED FROM THE PULSAR MAGNETOSPHERE, BUT THEY FAILED TO DETECT ITS X-RAY PULSATIONS. WE OBSERVED PSR J1836+5925 WITH THE XMM-NEWTON OBSERVATORY IN FEBRUARY 2013 WITH THE GOAL TO DETECT ITS X-RAY PULSATIONS AND STUDY THE THERMAL AND MAGNETOSPHERIC EMISSION WITH THE AID OF ENERGY-RESOLVED TIMING AND PHASE-RESOLVED SPECTROSCOPY. OUR PRELIMINARY ANALYSIS OF THE OBSERVATIONAL DATA HAS SHOWN THAT THE OBSERVATIONS WERE QUITE SUCCESSFUL. IN PARTICULAR, THANKS TO A LOW PARTICLE BACKGROUND, WE WERE ABLE TO DETECT THE X-RAY PULSATIONS. TO COMPLETE THE ANALYSIS, THE PULSATIONS IN DIFFERENT ENERGY BANDS AND THE SPECTRA IN DIFFERENT PULSE PHASE INTERVALS MUST BE STUDIED, THE X-RAY SPECTRUM AND PULSATIONS OF THE MAGNETOSPHERIC COMPONENT MUST BE COMPARED WITH THOSE IN GAMMA-RAYS, AND THE THERMAL COMPONENT MUST BE FIT WITH REALISTIC NEUTRON STAR ATMOSPHERE MODELS. IN ADDITION, THE INFERRED PROPERTIES OF THE PSR J1836+5925 EMISSION SHOULD BE COMPARED WITH THOSE OF SIMILAR PULSARS AND WITH THE THEORETICAL MODELS. TO COMPLETE THIS WORK, WE REQUEST A SUPPORT FROM THE 2014 ADAP. THIS STUDY WILL ADDRESS THE THERMAL EVOLUTION OF NEUTRON STARS AND THE MECHANISMS OF THE PULSAR MAGNETOSPHERIC EMISSION. IT WILL ADVANCE OUR UNDERSTANDING OF GENERAL PROPERTIES AND EVOLUTION OF NEUTRON STARS, WHICH REPRESENT THE END PRODUCT OF EVOLUTION OF A SIGNIFICANT FRACTION OF STELLAR POPULATION. THE SUBJECT OF THIS PROPOSAL IS RELEVANT TO THE FOLLOWING ASTROPHYSICS STRATEGIC OBJECTIVES IN THE 2014 NASA SCIENCE PLAN: "DISCOVER HOW THE UNIVERSE WORKS, EXPLORE HOW IT BEGAN AND EVOLVED" AND "EXPLORE THE ORIGIN AND EVOLUTION OF THE GALAXIES, STARS AND PLANETS THAT MAKE UP OUR UNIVERSE".

doc.ContractDescription: THE NEOPROTEROZOIC GLACIATIONS AT ~730 GA AND 610 GA ARE THOUGHT BY SOME GEOLOGISTS TO REPRESENT "SNOWBALL EARTH" EPISODES IN WHICH EARTH'S OCEANS WERE ENTIRELY FROZEN OVER. OTHER GEOLOGISTS ARGUE, HOWEVER, THAT PHOTOSYNTHETIC ALGAE AND CYANOBACTERIA COULD NOT HAVE SURVIVED SUCH EXTREME CONDITIONS. THIS HAS LED TO ALTERNATIVE MODELS IN WHICH STRIPS OF EITHER OPEN WATER OR THIN (METER-THICK) ICE EXISTED AROUND THE EQUATOR. THE OPEN WATER SOLUTION HAS BEEN TERMED THE "SLUSHBALL" MODEL BY ITS DETRACTORS AND THE "JORMUNGAND" STATE BY ITS PROPONENTS. JORMUNGAND WAS A MYTHICAL NORWEGIAN SEA SERPENT THAT WAS LARGE ENOUGH TO ENCIRCLE THE EARTH AND GRASP ITS OWN TAIL IN ITS MOUTH. THE PROPOSED WORK WILL ADDRESS TWO KEY QUESTIONS REGARDING THESE ALTERNATIVE MODELS FOR NEOPROTEROZOIC GLACIATION. FIRST, WHY DO SOME CLIMATE MODELS PREDICT OPEN WATER NEAR THE EQUATOR WHEREAS OTHERS PREDICT THIN ICE? THE DIFFERENCES PROBABLY HAVE TO DO WITH HOW VARIOUS ICE-RELATED PROCESSES ARE PARAMETERIZED IN THE MODELS, PARTICULARLY PENETRATIVE ABSORPTION OF SOLAR RADIATION WITHIN THE ICE. WE HOPE TO DEMONSTRATE THAT NO MORE THAN ONE TYPE OF ALTERNATIVE STATE IS PHYSICALLY POSSIBLE WHEN ICE PHYSICS IS PROPERLY TREATED. SECOND, ARE THESE SOLUTIONS STILL POSSIBLE WHEN SEA-GLACIER FLOW IS INCLUDED? THE TERM "SEAGLACIER" IS SHORTHAND FOR THICK SEA ICE THAT FORMS NEAR THE POLES AND FLOWS TOWARDS THE EQUATOR. SOME PREVIOUS STUDIES HAVE PREDICTED THAT SEA-GLACIER FLOW WILL ALWAYS PRECLUDE THIN-ICE/JORMUNGAND SOLUTIONS. OTHER STUDIES HAVE SUGGESTED THAT SUCH SOLUTIONS REMAIN POSSIBLE. ALL PREVIOUS STUDIES HAVE BEEN PERFORMED FOR OCEAN-COVERED PLANETS WITH NO EXPOSED CONTINENTS. TO ADDRESS THESE QUESTIONS WE WILL USE TWO DIFFERENT CLIMATE MODELS DEVELOPED ORIGINALLY BY ONE OF US (DP). THE SIMPLER MODEL IS AN ENERGY-BALANCE MODEL, OR EBM, IN WHICH THE GLOBE IS DIVIDED INTO A NUMBER OF DIFFERENT LATITUDE BANDS AND ENERGY BALANCE, INCLUDING DIFFUSIVE LATITUDINAL HEAT TRANSPORT, IS COMPUTED WITHIN EACH BAND. THE MORE COMPLEX MODEL IS A 3-DIMENSIONAL GLOBAL CLIMATE MODEL, OR GCM, WHICH SOLVES THE COMPLETE SET OF HYDRODYNAMIC EQUATIONS FOR THE ATMOSPHERE. BOTH MODELS INCLUDE A FULLY INTERACTIVE HYDROLOGIC CYCLE, ALONG WITH PARAMETERIZATIONS FOR SURFACE ALBEDO (E.G., SNOW AND ICE COVER) AND OCEAN HEAT TRANSPORT. THE BULK OF THE WORK WILL INVOLVE INCORPORATING PENETRATIVE SOLAR RADIATION AND SEA-GLACIER FLOW INTO THE 3-D CLIMATE MODEL. THE FIRST TASK CAN BE DONE USING A 2-STREAM RADIATIVE TRANSFER METHOD THAT HAS ALREADY BEEN IMPLEMENTED IN OUR EBM. THE SECOND TASK CAN BE DONE USING NUMERICAL TECHNIQUES DEVELOPED FOR STUDYING MODERN-DAY ICE SHELVES BUT MODIFIED TO ACCOUNT FOR SPHERICAL GEOMETRY. IMPORTANTLY, FRICTION BETWEEN THE FLOWING SEA-GLACIERS AND THE STATIONARY CONTINENTS IS EXPECTED TO REDUCE THE RATE AT WHICH THE GLACIERS FLOW DOWN INTO THE TROPICS, THEREBY MAKING IT EASIER FOR OPEN WATER (OR THIN ICE) TO PERSIST. THE RESULTS ARE EXPECTED TO DEPEND STRONGLY ON THE GEOMETRY OF THE CONTINENTS, SO DIFFERENT CONTINENTAL CONFIGURATIONS WILL BE USED (MODERN, NEOPROTEROZOIC, AND VARIOUS IDEALIZED STATES). BY ANALYZING THE RESULTS OF MULTIPLE NUMERICAL EXPERIMENTS, WE WILL DETERMINE WHETHER OR NOT SUCH BIOLOGICALLY FRIENDLY, ALTERNATIVE NEOPROTEROZOIC GLACIAL STATES MIGHT HAVE EXISTED. THIS, IN TURN, WILL LEAD TO AN IMPROVED UNDERSTANDING OF THE FACTORS LEADING TO THE EVOLUTION OF COMPLEX (ANIMAL) LIFE.

IGF::OT::IGF UNDER NASA'S GAME CHANGING DEVELOPMENT PROGRAM/NUCLEAR SYSTEMS KILOPOWER PROJECT, NASA GLENN RESEARCH CENTER (GRC) IS EXAMINING SMALL FISSION REACTORS FOR FUTURE SPACE TRANSPORTATION AND SURFACE POWER APPLICATIONS. THE REACTORS WOULD HAVE AN 8 TO 15 YEAR DESIGN LIFE AND COULD BE AVAILABLE FOR A 2020 LAUNCH TO SUPPORT FUTURE NASA SCIENCE MISSIONS. ADVANCED COOLING TECHNOLOGIES INC. (ACT) IS WORKING WITH NASA GRC ON BOTH THE HOT END AND THE COLD END THERMAL MANAGEMENT SYSTEMS OF A 1 KWE STIRLING SYSTEM (KILOPOWER). THE HOT END THERMAL MANAGEMENT SYSTEM CURRENTLY DEVELOPED BY ACT UNDER A PHASE II NASA SBIR, CONTRACT NNX13CC84C, CONSISTS OF ALKALI METAL HEAT PIPES THAT TRANSFER THE HEAT FROM THE REACTOR TO THE STIRLING CONVERTORS. ALTHOUGH THESE HEAT PIPES WILL BE USED ONLY FOR GROUND TESTING, THEY ARE DESIGNED TO WORK BOTH IN SPACE (WITH ARTERIAL SELF-VENTING WICK INSIDE) AND IN GRAVITY ASSISTED ORIENTATION, AS THERMOSYPHONS. THE DELIVERABLES OF THE CURRENT PHASE II PROGRAM, WHICH ENDS IN JULY 2015, WILL CONSIST OF 9 ALKALI METAL HEAT PIPES THAT WILL BE USED FOR THE GROUND TESTING OF THE KILOPOWER SYSTEM THAT IS ENERGIZED BY A REAL NUCLEAR REACTOR. SEVERAL ADDITIONAL TASKS WILL BE REQUIRED TO FULLY QUALIFY THESE SODIUM HEAT PIPES. FIRST, NASA GRC WANTS ADDITIONAL HEAT PIPES FOR LONG TERM LIFE TESTS OF THE ENTIRE REACTOR SYSTEM. IN ADDITION, THE ALKALI METAL HEAT PIPES IN A SELF-VENTING ARTERIAL CONFIGURATION HAVE NEVER BEEN TESTED IN MICROGRAVITY CONDITIONS. BASED ON THE EXPERIENCE AND LESSONS LEARNED DURING THE CURRENT PHASE II NASA SBIR, INNOVATIVE HIGH TEMPERATURE ALKALI METAL HEAT PIPES FOR SPACE , ACT IS PROPOSING A PHASE III PROGRAM, WHICH WILL DESIGN, FABRICATE AND TEST A FLIGHT LIKE ALKALI METAL SELF-VENTING HEAT PIPE WITH THE CORRESPONDING TEST SETUP FOR GROUND TESTING THAT SIMULATES TESTING AT ISS. PROCEDURES AND TRAVELERS FOR FABRICATING SELF-VENTING-ARTERY, ALKALI-METAL HEAT PIPES WILL BE INCLUDED. A PHASE IIE PROGRAM, RUNNING IN PARALLEL, WILL DESIGN, FABRICATE, TEST AND DELIVER 10 ADDITIONAL ALKALI METAL HEAT PIPES, FOR THE KILOPOWER LIFE TESTS
